document_data.History:
In his younger days, Henry worked with a [[hin]] rogue named [[Sagrais Bigelow]], who emptied pockets while the mage performed [[spell]]s and tricks as a distraction.

Henry the Shadow Master and Matilda the White Lady, his wife of forty years, retired to the Nellie Thursday Home for Experienced Adventurers together.{{Cite card/AD&D Trading Cards/1993|83|Matilda the White Lady}} However, the wizard enjoyed a good pipe too much and just ensorcelled himself with ''[[Henry's hide-a-smell]]'' to be unsmellable and continued to inhale [[pipeweed]] smoke in secret from his beloved wife. The spouses enjoyed their thirty years at Nellie Thursday in its elegant lodgings, and Matilda found its training area helpful in maintaining her physique.

At the age of eighty-eight winters, Henry, accompanied by his wife and several other geriatric adventurers, embarked on a quest to find [[Wemic the Wise]]'s old missing roommate. The quest ended up dragging them across several worlds, including{{Cite polyhedron/72/Experience Preferred, Part One|11}} the jungles of [[Quorsit]];{{Cite polyhedron/73/Experience Preferred, Part Two|7}} and the [[demi-plane]] of [[Kansas]], where he faced [[Simon (illusionist)|Simon the Illusionist]] in a duel and survived.{{Cite polyhedron/74/Experience Preferred, Part III|16}}
